Paratype
16/03

(female; 
Fig. 5
). Body glabrous, completely hairless.

Venter . Apex of labium reaching middle coxa. A narrow, slightly curved groove runs along the meso-metapleural junction, possibly representing peritreme of the opening of the scent gland apparatus. Sternite VII has a median and 2 (1+1) lateral projections directed posteriorly; median projection (not clearly visible) triangular, with a wide base, lateral projections have a wide triangular base continuing in a long narrow process pointed at the apex. Median projection represents the subgenital plate of segment VII ( Drake & Davis, 1960 ;
Heiss et al ., 2015
), but the suture between the plate and the basal part of the segment VII is not visible.
